  "strengths": [
    "Good Swirl unit that has his niche in Electro-Charge teams, being able to increase both his own Swirl damage and Electro-Charge itself.",
    "Utilizes Normal Attacks during his Nightsoul's Blessing state, allowing him to proc effects such as Xingqiu and Yelan's Elemental Bursts.",
    "Has access to flight, allowing him to bypass most melee attacks while in Nightsoul's Blessing. This also extends to making exploration more convenient for players.",
    "Brings sustain potential to the team with his on-hit healing from his tonicshots. This also has the added benefit of healing off-field characters."
  ],
  "weaknesses": [
    "Due to his passives particularly buffing Swirl and Electro-Charge, he does not truly contribute to a team's raw damage, and relies on the team comp itself to be effective.",
    "Lacks interruption resistance and can be staggered in the air with ranged attacks or a stray swipe from a long-reaching melee unit.",
    "Individual damage multipliers are low, relying more on Elemental Reactions. This also extends to his healing's multipliers, making him less effective than an actual healer.",
    "Elemental Burst only functions as a quick form of Crowd Control, but lacks a more impactful use aside from enemy interruption and swirling."
  ],
