  "strengths": [
    "Allows the Lunar-Charged reaction, which basically by itself is a stronger variant of Electro-Charged due to it having the ability to CRIT.",
    "Easy, simple-to-use, with a 100% uptime on both her off-field summon and shield, and she can even extend it indefinitely with her Elemental Burst. This makes her one of the more comfortable characters to use in the overworld and endgame combat.",
    "Stacking ATK benefits both her offensive and defensive utility, with decent scaling on her shields.",
    "Can buff herself and your active character's Elemental Mastery with her Elemental Burst.",
    "As Lunar-Charged can have Hydro and Electro co-exist to an enemy, Ineffa allows you to run other teams such as Hyperbloom or Overvape albeit slightly weaker than her intended teams."
  ],
  "weaknesses": [
    "As it is for characters with niche mechanics, team-building for Ineffa will require you to run a Hydro character in the team, although this weakness is only slightly less restrictive than previous niche DPS as she can flex to teams like Dendro as well, as long as Hydro exists.",
    "Because Lunar-Charged can CRIT and the damage is based on the characters who applied it, and since Ineffa optimally wants to Burst every rotation, balancing ATK, CRIT, Elemental Mastery, and Energy Recharge stats for Ineffa and her team is her real struggle."
  ],
